**2.**  **Feature Engineering :**

- --Libraries : NLTK , Scikit-Learn , Regular Expression
- --Notebook : TalentBait\_EDA.ipynb
- --Process of feature engineering  :

- Start by cleaning the text from  (signs , special characters  )
- Lemmatization &amp; Stemming
- Label Encoding
- Split the train and the test data
- Text representation :

Choosing TF-IDF Vectors feature ([short for term frequencyinverse document frequency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tf%E2%80%93idf))

- Chi squared test : see unigrams and bigrams most correlated with each label :

- -- &#39;none&#39; label:

-  Most correlated unigrams:

gute,standort,deutschland,gmbh,kenntnisse

- Most correlated bigrams:

ms office,gute kenntnisse

- --&#39;soft&#39; label:

-  Most correlated unigrams:

umgang,sap,office, ms,kenntnisse

-  Most correlated bigrams:

gute kenntnisse,ms office

- --&#39;tech&#39; label:

-  Most correlated unigrams: flexibilitt,hohe,kenntnisse,teamfhigkeit,arbeitsweise

- Most correlated bigrams:

hohes ma,wort schrift

**3. Model (Train &amp; Test) :**

- --Notebook : TalentBait\_Model2.ipynb
- --we&#39;ll try several machine learning classification models in order to find which one performs best on our data.
- --We will try with the following models:

- Random Forest
- Multinomial Nave Bayes
- Multinomial Logistic Regression
- Gradient Boosting

- --The methodology :

1 choose hyperparameters

2 Search Cross Validation process

3 Grid Search Cross Validation

4 Training &amp; Test

5 Calculate accuracy

Note the prediction classify the text and in addition give the the conditional probability of belonging to every label

6 Reporting the performance of each model and plot the confusion matrix to summarize

 the performance
